{
  "$schema": "https://openapi.vercel.sh/vercel.json",
  "_comment": [
    "Geopol-JP variant — Vercel deployment config.",
    "Use this as a SEPARATE Vercel project pointed at the same git repo.",
    "Either replace the upstream vercel.json with this one in the geopol-jp",
    "deployment project, OR keep both projects in the same repo and use",
    "Vercel's per-project Build Command override.",
    "",
    "Build Command:    npm run build:geopol-jp",
    "Output Directory: dist",
    "Install Command:  npm install",
    "",
    "Then in Vercel project Settings → Domains, attach your chosen domain.",
    "Recommended subdomains (hostname is what the variant detection keys off):",
    "  - geopol-jp.<your-domain>",
    "  - geopol.<your-domain>",
    "(Both prefixes are recognized by src/config/variant.ts.)"
  ],
  "buildCommand": "npm run build:geopol-jp",
  "outputDirectory": "dist",
  "framework": null,
  "rewrites": [
    {
      "source": "/((?!api|assets|favico|map-styles|data|textures|sw\\.js|workbox-[a-f0-9]+\\.js|manifest\\.webmanifest|offline\\.html|robots\\.txt).*)",
      "destination": "/index.html"
    }
  ],
  "headers": [
    {
      "source": "/api/(.*)",
      "headers": [
        { "key": "Access-Control-Allow-Origin", "value": "*" },
        { "key": "Access-Control-Allow-Methods", "value": "GET, POST, OPTIONS" },
        { "key": "Access-Control-Allow-Headers", "value": "Content-Type, Authorization, X-WorldMonitor-Key" }
      ]
    }
  ]
}
